INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_bea3700','letter','1780-08-06','Robinsons House','NY','US','Benedict','Arnold','','George','Washington','','individual','','On my arrival at this post, I found every thing thrown into great confusion, by the troops removing from hence, and the militia coming in.','ltr_bea3700.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_bea3701','letter','1780-08-08','Robinsons House','NY','US','Benedict','Arnold','','George','Washington','','individual','','I wish your Excellency would be kind enough to order Mr. Erskine to send me a map of the country from this place to New York, particularly on the east side of the river, which would be very useful to me.','ltr_bea3701.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_bea3702','letter','1780-09-11','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','Benedict','Arnold','','George','Washington','','individual','','I came here this morning, in order to establish signals, to be observed in case the enemy came up the river ; to give some directions respecting the guard-boats ; and to have a beacon fixed upon the mountain','ltr_bea3702.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_bea3703','letter','1780-09-12','Robinsons House','NY','US','Benedict','Arnold','','George','Washington','','individual','','The order, contained in the postscript of your Excellency\'s letter of the 7th, to send the eight bargemen of Colonel Putnam\'s regiment to join their regiment, I conceive to be on a supposition of their being idle at West Point.','ltr_bea3703.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_bea3704','letter','1780-09-14','Robinsons House','NY','US','Benedict','Arnold','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am, therefore, of opinion, that the Pennsylvania line, which I suppose to amount to twenty-five hundred or three thousand men, should hold themselves in readiness to march','ltr_bea3704.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_bea3705','letter','1780-09-16','Robinsons House','NY','US','Benedict','Arnold','','George','Washington','','individual','','My answers to the questions proposed by your Excellency to the Council of War I will do myself the honor to deliver in person.','ltr_bea3705.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
